    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-05-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 406/50–51.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 286.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch, No. 488, of December
                    24 last, stating that the Spanish minister to China has informed you that he is
                    unable to exchange notes with you, for the purpose of effecting an arrangement
                    for the reciprocal protection of American and Spanish trade-marks in China, I
                    inclose herewith for your information a copy of correspondence on the
                        subject<note n="a" xml:id="d208fna">Supra.</note> between the department and
                    our minister to Spain.</p>
                <p>It will be seen from Mr. Collier’s dispatch that the Spanish Government is
                    willing that such an exchange should be made.</p>
                <p>You will, therefore, bring the matter to the attention of your Spanish colleague,
                    and proceed with the exchange of notes.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
